</p>
<p>Finding the right words can be challenging, but even a simple, heartfelt message can offer comfort. Remember to keep the focus on the deceased and their positive qualities, celebrating their life and memory. Avoid overly formal language, and let your sincerity shine through. Your genuine expression of sympathy can provide a much-needed source of strength and comfort to those navigating their grief.</p>
    

